      "id": "0b9916d4_279aeb0d",
      "file_path": "gui-clamp/ui-react/src/components/dialogs/ControlLoop/CommissioningModal.js",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 135,
      "message": "I will add the local variable in the next patchset.\n\nWith the short foreach I am extracting the start values from the node templates. And then will use those start values to populate initial data in the json editor. But I am only taking those node templates that have common types associated with them. The backend common properties do not contain start values - so this is required.\n\nAs for the foreach loops used in other functions. I try to use them as little as I can. I will see if I can remove some of the foreach loops in other functions for the next patchset. They are sometimes needed here because I need to have the data in a particular format to be rendered nicely on the UI.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7603,
        "name": "Saul Gill",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "saul.gill@est.tech",
        "username": "saul.gill"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-28 14:33:53.000000000",
