    },
    {
      "id": "46068fc9_3f5490cd",
      "file_path": "gui-clamp/ui-react/src/components/dialogs/ControlLoop/CommissioningModal.js",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 135,
      "message": "basically, we're just making a copy of a Map, so why not use a copy constructor?.  In java, this particular chunk, for example, could be changed to something like:\n\n  shortenedNodeTemplatesObjectStartValues[key] = new HashMap<>(propertiesObject.properties)\n\nthis is shorter, AND it's more obvious what it's doing",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-28 18:07:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "0b9916d4_279aeb0d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "2439d41f_67e259d7",
      "file_path": "gui-clamp/ui-react/src/components/dialogs/ControlLoop/CommissioningModal.js",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 135,
      "message": "I have added the cached variable you suggested Jim.\n\nThe loops in the below functions - updateTemplate and makeSchemaForCommonProperties - \n\nThe former has to take the values entered by the user and \"fill them into\" the correct places in the full service template. I have to pick out particular items and place them in the correct places in the template. Foreach is just the most clean way to do this that I can see currently.\n\nIn the latter, I have to construct a schema locally in a very specific way so as to be understood by the json schema editor.\n\nCould we make the optimisations vis-a-vis loops and other elements in a future review?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7603,
        "name": "Saul Gill",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "saul.gill@est.tech",
        "username": "saul.gill"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-28 18:16:06.000000000",
